caption: Had dinner there recently. The food was pretty good and the waitress was awsome. My only compliant is that the place did not have proper heating. They should have had some portable heaters to make their customers feel conformable.
Worth every penny 👍🏼
I've been here several times and have never been disappointed. The food is fantastic, portions are perfect, service is friendly and their outdoor setup is wonderful.
Unbelievably delicious / authentic food, we got takeout and it was still top-notch quality.

Oh my goodness the food was amazing. I got the spring rolls and the crispy chicken 5 seed. Everything was so tasty! Apart from that, the decor was beautiful and so lively. It’s great for either date night, or dinner/lunch with friends. I can’t wait to go back!
So yummy - the perfect rainy day outdoor eating set up with a plastic covering and heat lamps! The food was fresh and delicious!!
The food was delicious. We ordered green curry and chicken fried rice. The place is well maintained and beautiful. Very good service.

Such a great spot! Service was quick and the food was excellent (we got the crispy roll, PCU and drunken lo mein). The flowers are beautiful & the music they had playing was so much fun! Can’t wait to go back!
The best Tom Yum soup in NYC!

Pretty mediocre Thai food. Got this for takeout. Rolls were very average and the crab fried rice was recommended by the person working at the restaurant and it was really bad... I actually didn’t feel good after it. Would not recommend if you’re looking for good Thai in the area, especially for takeout.
Delicious
(Translated by Google) PadThai to go, very bad plus the horrible smell. The normal fried squid.  (Original) PadThai to go , muy malo además el olor horrible .Los calamares fritos normales .
Ordered green curry and chicken fried rice. Both were really good.
The food is delicious and super fresh tasting. Definitely not your average Thai place. Plus the service is great and they made a beautiful outdoor dining space.

Very nice atmosphere with the outdoor seating, floral setup and smooth jazz playing in the background. The hot sake was tasty and exactly what it should be. Service was prompt and the food came out in a timely fashion. The food was unfortunately just average. The calamari was big box unfrozen and reheated. The shrimp pad Thai was good and we enjoyed that but the chicken fried rice was below average.. no flavor and quite bland. I really wanted to like this spot and I hope that we showed up on an off day since it’s the close of summer and there weren’t a lot of ppl out dining but I’m not sure if I would visit again.
Great food lovely staff. Open during covid and worth the visit. Can't wait to go back again honestly. Their lamb curry was great.
Very bad service.
Great Thai food! Clearly the best in the neighborhood. Really nice outdoor seating on the side street. Thai Ice Tea is something special

I celebrated my graduation yesterday in this great restaurant. I am glad to say that we enjoyed a pleasant evening and the place was definitely one of the reasons for the strong gathering. The stuff  helped in a pleasant manner, the cooking was appetizing and my guests were extremely  thrilled. We shall no dout come back again for more events. Thank you very much.

From the moment  you come to that place  the stuff gives you a good feeling. Very comfortable hosts, it is a happy place to  enjoy with friends and colleagues or with your date. Excellent  meals, professional  chief cook and stuff, reasonable  pay and professional  service. Warmly recommended.
They offer a great range of delicious food. I enjoyed eating here. Staff members are always very friendly, prices are reasonable and the spot is always neat.
Tried this spot before with my friend and I am obsessed ever since. I enjoy the excellent mood and delicious dishes and drinks. 5 stars from me.

I celebrated my birthday yesterday in this fine place. happy to tell that we passed a phenomenal evening and the venue was unquestionably the reason for the outstanding gathering. The waiters  participated in a gorgeous style, the food was very good and my friends were very  glad. We shall no dout come back again for more events. thanks very much.
Thai food yummy
Good food and great service. Best pad thai I've had. And trust me, I've had paid thai from at least eight thai restaurants in Brooklyn! And two in FiDi, NY!
Great food and service. We tried some of the seasonal items and immediately decided we had to come back to try more!
Interesting decor, definitely must try the Thai ice tea!

quaint place in the middle of brooklyn with palm leaves wallpaper.  went for lunch special - $12 with app & entree - that was just okay. The pad thai was sweet but nothing special.. I always look for the pop of flavor in thai food, and there was none. the service was good and they’re attentive.  sadly, no mango sticky rice for dessert!
Cute space and a great menu - not just the usual Thai fare, but some out of the ordinary dishes that turned out to be delicious (as were the more usual dishes). Excellent choice!
Stopped in for lunch with some co-workers. Cute space, good lunch specials. Had the panang curry with a side salad. Both hit the spot.
Great service and great food!

The atmosphere of the place is really nice. It's like someone who had been wanting to do a place like it got it done. I'd rather the paper menu not be on the table throughout meals because presumably it has to be discarded which is wasteful. Anyhow, it's like California meets Thai but more California. Food was good without really being great. I had the nut meal and didn't eat the nuts, it just didn't taste right with the meal but someone else may like it. Service was nice and polite. We'd visit again but not in a rush.
Delicious food! Everything I had on the menu has amazing. Great vibe and decor inside. Would definitely recommend to everyone.
The food for lunch was overall okay. The waitress had an attitude, unfriendly.
Delicious every time
(Translated by Google) The museum has a small area, half a basement, and has not been eaten here. Is it possible to know if the food is available?  (Original) 飧馆面积很小，半地下室，沒有在此进食过，未知食品是否可以。
Great Thai food. Check out the lunch specials.
(Translated by Google) Good address visiting Brooklyn Heights  (Original) Bonne adresse en visite à Brooklyn Heights

Great spot for all your usual Thai favorites plus some creative takes on classic dishes. Decent prices with quick, friendly and attentive service. Had the salmon over rice which was perfectly cooked, slightly crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside. The crab roasted inside a young cocounut was also delicious but should be ordered with a side of vegetables for some extra crunch and added nutrition.
Absolutely a spot worth stopping over, the food is excellent and fresh, the rates are affordable and it is always well kept there. Fantastic work.
The meals and service were above my expectations. We truly liked the ambience of this spot. Extraordinary restaurant to take the family out for lunch.
Cute atmosphere :) Food was also good!

Quaint and warm Thai place in Brooklyn. Basic Thai food menu, awesome starters. Almost everything off the menu is good. Must try drinks, specially the cocktails. Reasonably priced. Perfect spot for a date night!

Ordered beef salad & not even sure you can call it that since there was definitely greens that were past their prime. Just a few slices of beef, no cucumbers, tomato the dressing was so sweet! Don’t even ask about the wings :/
Go Brooklyn
Walked here for lunch. Was a recommendation. Saw it’s Grade Pending. Had to keep walking smh
Food was good but a little pricey
Food was very flavorful and delicious! I wasn’t a big fan of the cocktails, but overall very cute hole in the wall kind of place with great food!
Usually a wait but food is ok
Food lack thai tastes.  Service was poor. Felt invisible in the restaurant.
Relaxed vibe. But very disappointing Spicy Fried Chicken salad. Chicken was dry and bland. Salad was spicy but boring as it was only lettuce. The toasted rice is a powder...
The restaurant has cute and nice decor. The food was great. I had the beef salad and the dressing was sweet and sour which went well with the salad and the beef.
Very good food and a cozy spot for a midday meal
Fresh and tasty food and staff very pleasant, but they were very understaffed.
Third time here. The lunch special options are pretty good - and food is tasty.
Friendly service and tasty, aesthetically pleasing food. The Thai iced tea was spectacular! Prices were a little high, but quality was definitely good.
Good
Loved the black tea!!
Everything extra salty. Calamaris Italian style as opposed to thai. Very small portions. Keep away
Clean restaurant. Flavorful food. Clean restroom.
(Translated by Google) It is absolutely delicious, very well placed and the service is impeccable.  (Original) C'est absolument délicieux, très bien placé et le service est impeccable.
Food is never consistent. $25 with $5 tip that’s $30 for basil fried rice with chicken and shrimp at lunch.I don’t mind spending but I want what I pay for...

I really love this place. Had many interesting dishes that make it stand out from the many generic thai places you come across. My favorite for this place was  Thai peper beef and lamp Massaman,very good service
Small menu but good food and a nice cozy atmosphere
Modern Thai, Really friendly staff. Great food!
Minimal menu, great atmosphere, and solid flavors for their noodles. Looking forward to going back soon to try out their other options.
Blah Asian fusion.  Restaurant scene in Brooklyn heights badly needs shot in arm and this isn't it.
How do you mess up fried rice? 4x! Mushy rice with soggy tomatoes they should call it.
Have been there multiple times. Always great food. The lunch menu is highly recommended. A variety of bites for a good price in a nice atmosphere.
We had lunch at Pinto on a Wednesday. The place was not too crowded. The waitresses were very nice. The food came fast and was delicious

I don't rate it base on its Michelin status, the food is truly amazing. Everything melts in my mouth. The taste, the aroma and especially the atmosphere. The staff are nice and very efficient. I'll return to try other dishes next time. They do deserve a five-star rating.
(Translated by Google) A clean Thai restaurant  (Original) Temiz bir tayland lokantası
Service good.  Wonderful food and flavors.  Our group had lamb, crab and coconut friend rice, duck pho, shrimp and chicken Thai and appetizers.  Everything was fresh and tasty.
I went with my Thai friend and she totally approved the authenticity of the food. It was extremely good.
Still waiting for my food while all other 5 of my colleagues have been eating for a while. Couldn't even get cold water. Service is unbelievably slow!
Good food

I went here for my birthday and was plesantly suprised by how much I enjoyed this place! It was a very relaxing atmosphere and there are many selections on the menu to choose from. I got the thai dumplings for an appetizer and the chicken fried rice as an entree. Both eere exceptionally delicious and I would order either again. Though the place was a bit pricey, I thought it was worth it based on the quality of food!!
Food was good but a bit overpriced compared to other similar restaurants I've been to. The decor is really nice, and waiter was good.

4 stars because our waiter didn't pay enough attention to us. The food was great though. The lunch menu offered a lot of variety and our party of 3 all ordered something different . The food was tasty and presented well. We were especially impressed by the presentation of their version of the thai iced tea. Unfortunately we had to wait too long for the drink menu and the waiter never refulled our wayer glasses or came to check on us. For such a nice place we expected better service.
Menu font is too small, the lighting in the back is too dim, and the noise level is a bit high, but the food was really good.
Good food and service

The place itself is good. Good location, nice and clean place. The problem is the food here is disappointing. The sauce is thick, but there is little flavor in it. It has pretty much everything Thai food should have in its meal, but it just doesn't taste right...
Really nice food. I always test a place out by trying a staple (green curry, red curry etc.) and this place never disappoints.
Thai flavors and high quality ingredients finally come together.  Somehow though my takeout has come out better than dining in.
Very tasty Thai shrimp fried rice. Quiet place. They should have asked if I wanted a drink.

Not a huge selection but this little place serves tasty food. Lunch is classic Thai box lunch but without the box. Dinner is typical but tasty and done well.  The only liquor is wine and there's not much of a selection. There are steps down into it so not a good choice for people who have difficulty with stairs but there's not many of them.  The wait staff is attentive without hovering, which I like. It is also just a few blocks from the promenade overlooking the Brooklyn Bridge Park.  Overall it's a nice place for a quick, tasty, casual dinner & a pleasant evening stroll on the promenade overlooking the lower Manhatten skyline.
Very solid Thai place.
Absolutely love their green curry and their Thai iced tea is an event. Definitely one of the best restaurants in the neighborhood.
The yummiest green curry n Thai tea ever!

Great service with lots of plants in the restaurant and the also have vegan options. Doesn't necessarily ring a Thai restaurant with the music and decor (although lovely), their Pinto Tea (Thai Tea, photo attached) is amazing and is definitely worth trying.
Best Thai food  we've had so far, and lyche Bellini is amazing, #1 on my list of favorites.Definitely recommend to try!

Such an intimate classy little restaurant, with beautiful tables and seats + cute plants! The servers were so sweet and friendly! If you're getting curry, I recommend getting the wild mushroom & coconut soup to mix with it cause it's so delicious!  A La Panang ($14)- 3.5/5 I got the medium spicy and it was quite spicy.. had to start taking off my jacket and put my hair up! The spiciness starts to build up after each bite. It's really delicious mixed with coconut soup and less spicy. I wasn't too crazy about the veggies in it, I think it was zucchini and some random vegetables that I don't even know. The shrimp were good though. The brown rice came on the side and was okay, nothing special.  Crab Fried Rice in Young Coconut ($21)- 5/5 This was yummy! So much crab meat and the portion was quite big! They gave a little extra on the side too so my sister shared it with me. A little bit on the pricey side though for this dish.  Pinto Iced Tea ($6)- 5/5 This comes with ice cubes, cream, syrup and the tea itself. You pour the tea first, then add the cream! I didn't use any cream because it was seriously delicious the way it was and even before the milk! It was super fun and really good. Although it's very easy to finish and the portion is a bit small and also pricey iced tea. You can smash up the ice and make a slushie, which my server recommended me to do.  Creamy Tom Yum Soup ($8)- 3.5/5 This was sorta of the same Tom Yum soup I had in Thailand but a tad bit more sour. I loved the shrimp though! Portions are quite decent for the soup and they pour it at the table.  Wild Mushroom and Coconut Soup ($8) - 4/5 This was good, although still not the flavor I had when I went to Thailand. Really good coconut taste though.
Cool
This was an amazing place, loved the Thai iced tea

Terrible place!!!! We set down to have lunch and after we ordered the food we saw a RAT running around the dining area and in and out the kitchen. We left right away and we will never go back there again!!!

Thoroughly mediocre. My girlfriend got the crab fried rice baked in coconut - while the presentation was very unique, it was blander than generic Chinese takeout. Apps were overpriced for the average quality. My Panang curry was decent, but certainly nothing I’m excited to eat again

Green curry is really good here. I ordered take out AND dined in a few days after. The staff are all really attentive and friendly. They took care of my 15 people party for a work celebration. The wait for the food was a bit slow, and we got really hungry, but food was not disappointing. I got the green curry both times for lunch special.  For just $10 I get an app and delicious curry with rice? Yum. The restaurant has a serene decor and reminds me of a modern sleek bar.

Went for lunch, but we did not order the lunch special (price point for lunch seems a good deal, given the area). We had the calamari appetizer, lamb massaman curry, & the crab fried rice - shared everything between two. All three were tasty, but they weren’t exceptional. Good certainly, but no better than many neighborhood Thai/fusion places in the City - most of which are cheaper too. Spice was mild, & the hot sauce they offered wasnt zingy. Staff was pleasant & the food came out super fast (almost too fast).
Delicious Thai food. Very clean
Excellent service, affordable pricing, not usually crowded at all.  The Pad Thai was excellent - highly recommend.
Super good food. Must try the deconstructed Thai Iced Tea

Went there for lunch.  The lunch deals were excellent.  i was surprisingly satisfied with the tofu appetizer.  Get the Thai tea, which was fun to mix (and I’m glad they separated the milk and simple syrup because sometimes, it can be too sweet for me).  It was an overall great experience.
Delicious lunch specials
A cozy place and decent meal!
Discovered while walking through Brooklyn on way to entry to walk Brooklyn Bridge. Great fresh Thai food. Had chicken Sarah and diced chicken lettuce wraps
Very modern Thai food and great array of vegetarian options.

There is lots on the menu to choose from: Big dishes to small dishes. The prices are reasonable and there was enough seating for a dinner rush. I just wanted to check out the place so I tried the Garlic BokChoy. I found it a bit chewy and wasn't a fan of the vinegar oil used. Yes, it left a salty after taste. However the stir-panned garlic was crunchy. The place had higher prices than other area Thai restaurants. Quick and Friendly staff! My food was out like a fast food restaurant. Dim lighting  which made it hard to read the menu which wraps around the napkin. The place   was quaint with flowers and wood.  There is a side entrance for wheelchairs where as the front has steps.

I had coconut crab fried rice and a side order of sauté greens. The latter was very salty and could not be consumed on its own.  Fried rice was good though a tad on the oily side.  Very friendly staff and prompt service.

Omg....I experienced extreme fatigue and dizziness after having their signature creamy Tom yum soup..and green curry lunch special.... I felt like I also fainted in front of my work desk...I can't imagine how much salt and MSG they've added to their food that caused me the "Chinese restaurant syndrome" will not return back to this restaurant...
White people Thai..not very spicy.. decent but not extraordinary
Nice eatery good ambiance

I happened to pass by Pinto one evening with a friend and then decided to stop in for a bite to eat. We had a taste for Thai food yet wanted to try something new since I've been to Lantern on several ocassions.  The ambiance wasn't really to my liking since I prefer an authentic Thai flair.  However, again we decided to try something new. First, it took some time for our server to take our order. When she finally came her responses were somewhat curt and she seemed a bit impatient as we asked questions about the menu.  Our meals arrived and I mut say I was unpleasantly surprised. The service was poor as well as the food. I will never return nor recommend this place to anyone.
Delicious food at reasonable prices, child-friendly

A smaller place, but some of the best Thai food I've had. The staff is lovely and present (maybe sometimes too present--they came to my table one too many times to check in), but willing to answer questions about the menu. Food came quickly as well. Ambiance/restaurant setting is great, good place to meet a friend and have conversation without having to shout. Overall, would definitely recommend to a friend!
I recommend this place!
Great food. Good vibes

This place is "pricey" to some but the quality of the food is amazing. I just had the thai iced tea and omg it's so good. It's a must have. Crispy rolls were great. The lime and chipotle mayo sauce really made this dish and the shell was sooo crispy. I had the Lamb Massaman. Partner had the pumpkin curry (w. Chicken). They're both so mouth watering. Would recommend everything I just had  Edit: forgot to comment about the wonderful service

literally and completely unexpected, this place had the best customer service I have ever experienced at a nyc / Brooklyn thai restaurant.  the menu was quaint and to the point, design and layout was elegant and seemed to steer clear of the Thailand wooden jungle or the over popular industrial themes. It was like walk into a thai appreciation french restaurant.
Nice staff very nice place food is really not that great went at night place was not very well lit had hard time seeing menu I would recommend this place if you are into the Brooklyn Restaurant Hype
I like this place.  The fried rice was delicious.  I will definitely go back.
Selections for the vegans and non-vegans in our group. Delicious food. Terrific service too.
Very Dim Lighting so it's hard to read the menu. Food isn't very tasty but the presentation is good. Very friendly staff.
Amazing, affordable thai. Get the green curry, just beware the highly erratic spice options

The food is always delicious, served quick, staff is very friendly, very creative drink selection, although small, and if you love classic house music like I do, a great selection of music to groove to while you dine!
Amazing. Just amazing. Great food.  Awesome food. Clean and uncluttered atmosphere. Good service. And, by the way, amazing food. "Elevated Thai".
Lovely place! Service was very friendly and attentive, Pad Thai was delicious and tasty. Definitely will come back.
Smashing! Great  and Excellent Customer Service. I'll definitely make it a point to come back again. Highly recommended.
Really good spot. Food was delicious, portions were good, service was attentive.

Lovely little place for a date night. The service is extremely fast, almost too fast to be true. The food isn't disappointing. The portions are perfect for 1. Although the food could be a little more warm. They also have a limited selection of wines which goes well with the food.  The dessert options are limited. We tried the berry panacotta and it was alright. I sent mine back coz I didn't want it with honey which wasn't mentioned on the menu, so you can decide accordingly. Romantic ambience and very friendly staff.
Pretty tasty Thai. Decent serving sizes. The setting is intimate... Wish I went here on a date night rather than a family dinner!
Great place for getting Thai if you're in the area. Unique Thai iced tea and all the dishes are solid.
Great Taste
I love this place. It is elegantly decorated, clean lines as well spotlessly clean.  The food is always served hot and fast and tasty.
Delish, great service, nice decor.
Delicious and easily the best lunch special I know of in the area. $9 for an appetizer and main course. Highly recommended.
The best Thai food on Montague Street. The restaurant is quiet and relaxed, the food is delicious, and the wait staff is superb.
Well prepared freshly prepared Thai food with descent portions of nicely presented dishes. Nice fit s change of pace.
Farm to table with a Thai twist. BYOB, great ambiance.
Delishhhh Food is so tasty better than lantern!

Amazing family style Thai.  So fresh and tasty.  The pumpkin curry is incredible.  Service also super friendly.   By far one of the best restaurant on Montague and It makes you rethink how good Thai food can be.  A must visit
